Plane Crashes Into Homes, Kills 10 Near New Delhi, Express Says

-- B y   B i b h u d a t t a   P r a d h a n
-- 
2011-05-26T04:37:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/plane-crashes-into-homes-kills-10-near-new-delhi-express-says.html
A turbo-prop aircraft ferrying a
critically ill man to a hospital in New Delhi crashed in a
residential area near  India â€™s capital, killing 10 people,
including all seven on board, the  Indian Express  reported.  The single-engine PC-12 aircraft was manufactured in 2005
by  Pilatus Aircraft  Ltd. of  Switzerland , the paper said, without
citing anyone. It left the city of Patna, in eastern Bihar state,
around 8.30 p.m. yesterday and crashed in the town of Faridabad
at around 10.46 p.m., the newspaper said. The aircraft was owned
and operated by New Delhi-based  Air Charter Services  Pvt. Ltd.,
it said.  The dead included a newly-married couple who were in the
house on which the plane fell, the report said, citing Faridabad
Mayor Ashok Arora. On board were doctors and nurses looking
after the sick patient, the paper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
